  "text": "[7] Profiling floats are of the ALACE type: they drift at depth, like acoustic floats, but return frequently to the surface where they are located by satellite [CITATION_1] . With 11-day cycles, they generally provide 10-day displacements at depth, estimated from surface fixes. They also profile temperature and salinity during the ascents. Besides the original profiling ALACE (or P-ALACE), several versions (APEX, PROVOR, SOLO, . . .) are now in use within the ARGO project, whose aim is to cover the whole ocean with at least 1 float in every 3°Â 3°square.",
